    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In multispectral imaging, images simultaneously obtained of an object at different wavelengths are made into a composite that displays the discrete spectral bands as colors. The resulting color patterns can be used to identify surface features.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
